          <h1>Version 2.3</h1>
          <ul>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="addition">Addition</span> Massive improvements to the image editor. You can now resize the box with handles, scroll to zoom the image, and pan by clicking on the image.</li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="addition">Addition</span> There is now an indicator to show which color you have selected in the editor.</li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="addition">Addition</span> You now receive an error message if the screenshot couldn't be saved on your system.</li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="change">Change</span> Improved memory performance. </li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="fix">Fix</span> Fixed numerous image editor bugs including some resetting after an abort, and some images showing up as garbage data if you attempted to crop them twice.</li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="fix">Fix</span> Fixed bug causing lines to be drawn when users moved text in drawing mode.</li>
            <li class="changelog-item"><span class="fix">Fix</span> Fixed bug causing Linux updates to fail if you didn't have permissions to unzip in your installation folder. Polkit now asks for permission.</li>
          </ul>
          <br />

        </main>
